OL,6,FThey returned with their verdict on
OL,7,FFriday after six hours and 49 minutes
OL,8,Fof deliberations in total.
OL,10,FMr Owens told the jury that the BBC
OL,11,Fhad put forward the position that Mr
OL,12,FAdams had "no reputation at all" and
OL,13,Fthe broadcaster had argued to the jury
OL,14,Fthat it should award only nominal
OL,15,Fdamages, putting forward the option of
OL,16,Fjust one euro.
OL,18,FMr Adams' team had argued that the
OL,19,Fdefamation fell within the "very
OL,20,Fserious" or "exceptional" end of the
OL,21,Fdamages scale.
